ce:section.ce:para:
Fig. 2
(a) shows the PXRD patterns of the CQDs prepared using LJ, CS, MS, and ML, which are carbonized at a temperature of 140 ̊C for 3 h. As evident from the figure, a broad diffraction peak at the (002) plane (JCPDS no 08–0415) was observed, which was attributed to the formation of amorphous and small-sized CQDs [20]. However, a (101) plane exhibited the graphitic nature of carbon formed during the synthesis of CQDs (JCPDS no 75–1621). A clear shift in the peak position for different precursors was noticed, which might be due to the presence of N and O in the precursors [39
]. Fig. 2(b) represents the FTIR spectra of the prepared CQDs recorded in the range 500–4000 cm-1. The spectra revealed bands 3405–3269 cm-1, owing to the -OH/NH stretching bond. In addition, the hydrogen bond in the range 2990–3500 cm-1 for LJ CQDs was dominating when compared to other CQDs [40]. The bands 1401–1411 cm-1 and 2914–2945 cm-1 correspond to CH bending mode, whereas the 1609–1704 cm-1 band is attributed to CO bond. An Additional band at 1180 cm-1 attributing to the CO bond in LJ CQDs was observed. The CN stretching bond was detected in the 1035–1098 cm-1 range. The band at 670 cm-1 was commonly observed in all the CQDs and corresponds to the CH stretching mode [13,39]. Fig. 2(c) shows the Raman spectra of the synthesized CQDs. The highly intense d-band at 1390 cm-1 represents the lattice disorder and structural defects attributed to sp3 hybridization in CQDs [41]. Whereas crystalline and graphitic structures result in a G-band at 1530 cm-1, which correspond to sp2 hybridization [39]. The CS CQDs have exhibited low intense D and G bands amongst all the CQDs due to the presence of functional groups on the surface of the carbon. Furthermore, to understand the degree of disorder or defects, the intensity ratio of d-band and G-band (ID/IG) of the LJ, CS, MS, and ML QCDs was estimated and was found to be 0.890, 0.971, 0.909, and 0.923, respectively. Wang et al. [42] also estimated the D to G band intensity ratio around 0.75, which was very much less than 1, indicating a less degree of defects. Whereas, in the present work, our samples showed a band intensity ratio close to 1, exhibiting the presence of a greater number of amorphous carbon in the prepared CQDs.
